    "recap_headline": "University of Alabama at Birmingham Athletics",
    "recap_text": "AUBURN\n\u2013 Auburn (14-2) used four home runs and totaled eight extra base hits to power its way to a 17-2 victory over UAB (10-7) on Tuesday night. The Tigers outhit the Blazers, 16-3.\nAuburn got out front early with four runs in the bottom of the first. Chase Fralick scored Bristol Carter by way of a fielder's choice. Eric Guevara singled home Chris Rembert to put the Tigers up, 2-0. The McCraine brothers, Brandon and Mason, drove home the latter two runs of the inning to give the Tigers a 4-0 advantage through one.\nThe Green and Gold answered back with two runs in the top half of the second.\nAndrew Hunt\ntrotted home thanks to a\nWesley Helms\nsac fly to right.\nBaylor Roberts\nknocked in\nBrady Waugh\ncourtesy of an Auburn error to cut the deficit to 4-2.\nAuburn got those two runs back in its half of the second inning. After a bunt single by Bristol Carter, Chase Fralick got the 3-0 green light and hit his fifth home run of the season to put the Tigers up, 6-2.\nFive more runs crossed for Auburn in the bottom of the third. Chris Rembert drove in two on a double to left center. Back-to-back home runs, a 2-run home run by Eric Guevara and a solo shot by Bub Terrell put the Tigers up, 11-2 after three innings of play.\nAuburn got a single tally in the bottom of the fourth after a leadoff hit by pitch came around to score from first on a Mason McCraine double.\nThe sixth-ranked Tigers got five more runs in the bottom of the fifth. Mason McCraine drove in his second run of the night on a sac fly to score Eric Guevara. Two batters later, Lucas Steele hit his first home run of the season for a grand slam to put Auburn up, 17-2.\nNOTES\n- The 17 runs allowed is the first time UAB has allowed 15+ runs since April 27, 2024 (Charlotte, 15 runs).\n- The Blazers turned their 17th double play which leads the American Conference.\n-\nBaylor Roberts\nincreased his hit streak to seven games.\n- With his second inning hit,\nBrady Waugh\nupped his on-base streak to 10 games.\nUAB returns home for its final non-conference series as the Blazers play host to Belmont. Friday's game is at 5 p.m., Saturday is slated for 2 p.m., and the series finale will be Sunday at 1 p.m. All games will be streamed on ESPN+.\nFOLLOW THE BLAZERS\nFor more information on the UAB Baseball team, follow @UAB_Baseball on X and Instagram.\nCompetitive Excellence Fund\nIn the current landscape of college athletics, the Competitive Excellence Fund has become integral in our department's mission to Win Champions, Graduate with Honors, and Impact the community. Through your generosity, our coaches will have the greatest opportunity to recruit, retain, and resource talented student athletes worthy of wearing a UAB uniform.\nClick here\nor connect with Blazer Boosters on how you can continue to fuel success."
